CANADA'S PRIME MINISTER may not have an easy campaign ahead; we sit down with Justin Trudeau to discuss his tenure so far. The country’s role as a liberal bastion seems safe, for now. Bayer is now reckoning with the problems presented by its latest acquisition, Monsanto—and it may emerge stronger. And, we meet The Hu, a Mongolian band on a heavy-metal mission. (Additional track: “Remember Your Thunder” courtesy of SnakeBiteSmile.) Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn